<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="183" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[136,1452,1526,1877]" pageId="3" pageNumber="183">
In the protologue of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pohl" authorityYear="1833" box="[369,541,1526,1552]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Luehea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="3" pageNumber="183" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="macrophylla">
<emphasis box="[369,541,1526,1552]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="183">L. macrophylla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
no reference is made to a specific specimen. Pohl’s original collection is kept in W where he worked and lived (
<bibRefCitation author="Stafleu, F. A. &amp; Cowan, R. S." box="[492,756,1562,1588]" pageId="3" pageNumber="183" refId="ref8497" refString="Stafleu, F. A. &amp; Cowan, R. S. (1976 - 1988) Taxonomic Literature: A selective guide to botanical publications and collections with dates, commentaries and types, 2 nd ed., Smithsonian Libraries, last updated 28 Jun. 2012. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 48631" type="book" year="1976">Stafleu &amp; Cowan 1976</bibRefCitation>
–1988: 315). We found only 
<specimenCount box="[1081,1248,1562,1589]" pageId="3" pageNumber="183" type="generic">two specimens</specimenCount>
of 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:039287B9FFDAFFA7FF43FAD7FBBFF8A4:8EE46074FFDAFFA7FACDF98BFA87F9C5" box="[1286,1356,1562,1588]" country="Brazil" municipality="Both" name="Pohl's" pageId="3" pageNumber="183">Pohl’s</location>
original collection with the name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pohl" authorityYear="1833" box="[416,586,1598,1624]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Luehea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="3" pageNumber="183" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="macrophylla">
<emphasis box="[416,586,1598,1624]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="183">L. macrophylla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
preserved in this herbarium. 
<collectingMunicipality box="[911,965,1598,1624]" pageId="3" pageNumber="183">Both</collectingMunicipality>
specimens were collected by 
<collectorName box="[1297,1348,1598,1624]" pageId="3" pageNumber="183">Pohl</collectorName>
in 
<collectingCountry box="[1383,1451,1598,1624]" name="Brazil" pageId="3" pageNumber="183">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(
<collectorName box="[146,291,1634,1660]" pageId="3" pageNumber="183">B. Wallnöfer</collectorName>
, pers. comm.), and are 
<typeStatus box="[551,649,1635,1661]" pageId="3" pageNumber="183">syntypes</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pohl" authorityYear="1833" box="[686,856,1634,1660]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Luehea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="3" pageNumber="183" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="macrophylla">
<emphasis box="[686,856,1634,1660]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="183">L. macrophylla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. They have labels mentioning the location congruent with the protologue, and Pohl’s handwriting (
<collectorName box="[661,809,1670,1696]" pageId="3" pageNumber="183">B. Wallnöfer</collectorName>
, pers. comm.), but the page and illustration numbers of the species publication are erroneous and correspond to the description and illustration of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pohl" authorityYear="1833" box="[1162,1327,1706,1732]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Luehea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="3" pageNumber="183" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="microphylla">
<emphasis box="[1162,1327,1706,1732]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="183">L. microphylla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, these specimens are 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pohl" authorityYear="1833" box="[367,537,1742,1768]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Luehea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="3" pageNumber="183" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="macrophylla">
<emphasis box="[367,537,1742,1768]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="183">L. macrophylla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and agree well with the vegetative and reproductive description presented in the protologue. For this reason, in accordance with Arts. 9.3 and 9.4 of the ICN, we have designated herein the specimen 
<emphasis box="[136,238,1814,1840]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="183">Pohl s.n.</emphasis>
(W0071385) as the 
<typeStatus box="[478,581,1814,1840]" pageId="3" pageNumber="183">lectotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pohl" authorityYear="1833" box="[623,796,1814,1840]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Luehea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="3" pageNumber="183" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="macrophylla">
<emphasis box="[623,796,1814,1840]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="183">L. macrophylla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, by choosing the most complete specimen. 
<collectorName box="[1305,1349,1814,1840]" pageId="3" pageNumber="183">The</collectorName>
name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pohl" authorityYear="1833" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Luehea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="3" pageNumber="183" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="macrophylla">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="183">L. macrophylla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been considered a synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="A. St." authorityName="A. St." box="[675,873,1850,1876]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Luehea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="3" pageNumber="183" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rufescens">
<emphasis box="[675,811,1850,1876]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="183">L. rufescens</emphasis>
A.St.
</taxonomicName>
- 
<collectorName box="[881,926,1850,1876]" pageId="3" pageNumber="183">Hil.</collectorName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Schumann, K." box="[940,1127,1850,1877]" pageId="3" pageNumber="183" pagination="117 - 200" refId="ref8376" refString="Schumann, K. (1886) Tilliaceae. Flora Brasiliensis, enumeratio plantarum in Brasilia hactenus detectarum: quas suis aliorumque botanicorum studiis descriptas et methodo naturali digestas partim icone illustratas 12 (3): 117 - 200. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 454" type="journal article" year="1886">Schumann 1886</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
